      "writtenOn": "2020-12-28T17:21:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure how SkSL would know what we want. I think we always want \"aaaa\" on the coverage side. For color it\u0027s often the case that we want kDstIn or kSrcIn depending on whether an SkImage is alpha-only. We implement this in in some places by manipulating paint colors and texture swizzles, particularly when using ops that sample textures in the GS. Just specifying a SkBlendMode might be cleaner and more flexible. Using FPs rather than GPs would make that easier.",
